Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
editAddRoute(25.10)                                        editAddRoute(25.10)

Name
       editAddRoute - Creates a wire segment that starts or ends at the speci-
       fied coordinates

Syntax
       editAddRoute

       [-help]

       <point>

       Creates  a  wire  segment  that starts or ends at the specified coordi-
       nates. Splits diagonal wires  whose  width  is  greater  than  the  LEF
       MAXWIDTH parameter for that layer as they are drawn.

       If  required,  the tool allows you to change the net order while adding
       wire segments. Check the Examples sections for details.

       Note: Before running any Wire Editor  command,  all  objects  and  pre-
       routed wires/vias must be colorized already.

       If  you  do not want to view flight lines between Power and Ground (PG)
       wires and pins when drawing PG nets, use setLayerPreference  flightLine
       -isVisible 0 to turn off the display of these flightlines. editAddRoute
       as well as editCommitRoute honor this setting.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each editAddRoute parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man editAddRoute

       <point>
              Specifies  the  x  and  y coordinates for the start point or end
              point of the wire segment.

              Note that if the points you specify with each successive editAd-
              dRoute command are not aligned vertically or  horizontally,  the
              tool  adjusts the coordinates to align the end point of one seg-
              ment with the start point of the next segment.

Example
              * The following commands create wire  segments  that  start  and
                stop  at  the  specified points. The complete wire ends at the
                point specified by editCommitRoute.

                editAddRoute 33.392 36.831    #Start of first wire segment

                editAddRoute 32.985 32.766     #End  of  first  wire  segment,
                start of second

                editAddRoute 18.064 32.115    #End of second wire segment

                editAddRoute 20.951 27.073    #End of third wire segment

                editCommitRoute 20.992 27.114 #End of wire

              * Use  the  following  set of commands to add wire segments with
                different orders of nets:

                uiSetTool addWire

                setEditMode -layer_horizontal M10

                setEditMode -nets { a b c d e f}

                setEditMode -wire_override_spec  {{1  0.062  0.128}  {2  0.062
                0.1900}  {3  0.062  0.128} {4 0.062 0.1900} {5 0.062 0.128} {6
                0.062 0.1900} }

                editAddRoute {1000 2500}

                editAddRoute {1100 2500}

                setEditMode -layer_vertical M9

                #Change Net Order

                setEditMode -nets { a c b d f e}

                setEditMode -wire_override_spec  {{1  0.082  0.228}  {2  0.082
                0.2900}  {3  0.082  0.228} {4 0.082 0.6680} {5 0.082 0.228} {6
                0.082 0.2900} }

                editAddRoute {1100 2600}

                editCommitRoute {1100 2600}

